@friend_shape Finally, setting goals around a category of books helps motivate when the desire for the pure joy of reading isn’t as readily present. So, like, Pulitzer books. Or newbery books. Or a series or something like that.

@friend_shape Also reading short books is good for me since the investment feels lower and the accomplishment rush is quicker. Also, reading many books at once (diff genres) helps me dive into a book when I’m not feeling in the mood for the one book I’m trying to read.

@friend_shape Audio books during menial chores that don’t require a ton of brain power. And practicing listening at faster speeds, often helps me with the attention drift. I have to focus harder to listen. I really enjoy a book at about 2x speed. Sometimes the narration necessitates slower.
